Oops, that’s a pic of me, not a cocktail. I’m holding one tho so still counts.
But while I got ya here, just wanted to relay a friendly reminder on behalf of the state of California, your fellow neighbor, and all of humanity really:
WEAR A DAMN MASK!
I know they are kinda inconvenient and uncomfy for some, but ya know what else is inconvenient and uncomfortable? Sitting inside your house for days while everything is closed because this virus keeps spreading due to people not taking this mask thing seriously.
Like imagine if a doctor was just like “Nah, not gunna wear a mask during this open heart surgery cuz it’s a little uncomfortable.” Be safe and responsible and consider those around you, even if you aren’t very afraid of the virus yourself. If you’re out and in close proximity to others, cover that face, no matter how good it be lookin.
Plus, masks actually have a few perks:
1) They can make you feel like a ninja
2) Can be a nice accessory to compliment your fit
3) You can store little fruit snacks in them for a convenient snack on the go (haven’t tried but just thought of it)
If we all do our part to slow the spread, we can beat this thing!
Cheers to the weekend and stay safe out there everyone! (By wearing a mask of course)

It was so nice to meet the lovely and talented artist/muralist, @katetova yesterday (Pictured on right looking down at photos I lamely tried to take for her on her cell phone). Her mural at 347 Fillmore Street is called "Say Her Name" in honor of #breonnataylor

Want to go out but can’t get your kids to wear a mask? Here’s 5 tips that will help you!
I’ve heard people complaining about having to wear masks. But it is so necessary to protect yourself and others!
When it comes to my loved ones’ safety and health, especially if it’s about my daughters, I will do EVERYTHING within my power to protect them. Everything!
Wether it is washing our hands frequently 🧼, maintaining social distancing 👋🏼, or wearing a mask 😷 , you bet I will do it.
Here are 5️⃣ tips that will help your kids feel better wearing a mask:
1. Make sure it’s the right size, not too big not too small. This way it will be a bit more comfortable and safe.
2. Get a mask with a design, character or pattern they’ll love. My daughters are into unicorns 🦄 so I got them this cute mask.
3. Combine the mask with their outfit. This will make it more exciting!
4. Get matching masks for the family! You can even plan a 📸 photo shoot! Make it a big deal!
5. LEAD BY EXAMPLE. Understand the importance of wearing a mask, talk to them about why you are wearing it, and most importantly WEAR YOUR MASK 😷 and do it without complaining. They will follow your steps.
How do you #SlowTheSpread? Remember, #YourActionsSaveLives!
For more info click here:
https://covid19.ca.gov/
Drop a picture of your kids with their masks! I would love to see them! :)

Wrapping up memories from our camping trip in Holcomb Valley, Big Bear, CA with this little video from our bike 🚲 ride on the Alpine Pedal Path. ⁣
⁣
The Alpine Pedal Path is a paved bike and walking trail on the north shore of Big Bear Lake with wonderful views ⛰ and lake access. Although it was a holiday weekend, we lucked out with nearly no one else on the path! I think what helped was that it was 1) Sunday and many people were probably heading home from the weekend, 2) between 12 and 2pm, so the adjacent campground was empty between check out and check in 3) people may have been taking a break/ home for lunch. ⁣
⁣
Jason and the boys brought their own bikes, but I rented one from Paddles and Pedals.  We took our masks off when there weren’t  other people close by, and had them readily available to put back on - but in general, we wear masks 😷 even when we’re outside. *Notably, SoCal has seen significant rise in COVID19 cases since this trip (2 weeks ago), so we now wear our masks 100% when biking. #recreateresponsibly #slowthespread⁣
⁣
Family Video Tip:  Do you make family vacation videos? I have so many video clips on my 📱, but don’t always have time to do anything with them.  I sometimes motivate and make videos in iMovies, but I have two easier video making hacks to share!⁣
 ⁣
iPhone users:⁣
1.  Select the photos and videos in your camera roll to include in a short movie ⁣
2. Create an album - ie “Alpine Pedal Path”⁣
3. Open the album, select all, then press the > arrow on the right hand corner. A little video will be automatically created!⁣
4. I usually like to edit this further, but the smart technology is a time-saving start! To edit, open the video and find an “edit” button on the upper right corner. It’ll then add to your memories. ⁣
5. From there you can change the music, add photos/ videos, and adjust the duration. ⁣
6. You don’t have as much control as you would if you made the video in iMovie, but it is a LOT faster! ⁣
⁣
Did you know that you can save your instagram stories? Sometimes on trips, I’ll  save my stories at the end of the each day (lower right corner ... - “save video”), and voila - home video is done ✅ !

Took a COVId 19 Test this am so I can deliver this babe this week... 😷😷😷
.

Ryan got tested too so that way if I test positive and the hubby test negative, then he can take the baby home and I will have to quarantine in a different room by myself away from the family and just breastfeed with the mask and gloves. These are crazy, unprecedented times and to be honest they add an extra layer and stress to the normal labor and delivery of a baby.
.
🙏 🤞for everything to go smoothly. “I spent too much time with my kids” said no one ever!!! 💯💗

Seriously I have to keep reminding myself of this every time it feels like there is no end to this pandemic, when the news hit that schools will stay closed, and when we are pretty much back to shut down here in California...

Summer 2020. 🏖 We’ve never been to the beach more often. We have this beach in out backyard and never appreciated it. Kids are having the best summer ever. How lucky I am to spend every day with these monkeys? So thankful for all the health heros, essential workers that work day in and day out, so that we can spend our days pretty much living our best life. Sorry for ever complaining!!! 🙏🏼 

My job has been reduced to online workout and yoga classes. But seriously how lucky and blessed am I to be able to do that?

Hiiiii, WEAR A MASK 😷 
⁣
If you aren’t wearing a mask every-time you go outside, I want you to please read this post. And even if you are wearing a mask, tag someone who needs a reminder or share this message in hopes it reaches those who need to be reminded. 
⁣
We are still in a pandemic. A global pandemic that has no end in sight. It’s going to take alllll of our cooperation.  We need to let science catch up and play our part by being good global citizens - for not only ourselves, but for our local communities and for the entire human race. 
⁣
Use your mask as a badge of honor. “I protect you, you protect me” a symbol  of solidarity- as we fight this pandemic together. 
⁣
Yes. We can all agree, masks are less than ideal. But masks are WAY easier to breathe through than ventilators. 
⁣
I’m not sure how else to explain that it’s important to care about other people - especially right now. Maybe no one you know is sick, or you don’t feel at risk- but maybe the woman passing by you in the parking lot takes care of her elderly parent. Maybe that child in front of you in line has an auto immune condition. 

It’s important to take extra precautions and watch out for not only ourselves, but for all those around us. 
⁣
Please remember, your actions saves lives and by wearing a mask, you can help slow the spread of Covid-19. 

#youractionssavelives #stopthespread

Turn an old necklace into your mask holder! Such a simple DIY but makes a huge difference to have your mask at the ready, around your neck in the form of a necklace! I also made these for the girls because, they are very good at loosing their masks, but not anymore ;) ⁣⁣⁣
What you need:⁣⁣⁣
-Mask⁣⁣⁣
-Necklace or Chain (ideally 14-16” long)⁣⁣⁣
-Jewelry Pliers⁣⁣⁣
-Lobster claw clasp ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
All you have to do, is take your pliers and open up the final loop on your necklace. Thread the lobster claw clasp through the loop and then close the loop by squeezing it closed with the pliers! Now you have a clasp on both sides of your necklace, so you can attach it to your mask! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
The nice thing about using the lobster claw clasp is that you can easily remove the chain and place it on a different mask whenever you like! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
*Before ordering your clasps (they have them on Amazon) check the size of your mask straps to make sure you are getting a big enough clasp since they come in different sizes! #masknecklace #maskchain #diy #covidcrafting #wearthemask

I've never shared my beautiful friend, Angela Paul or her brilliantly written posts on my timeline before.
But, this time I will because we're all in this mask vs mask debate which, by now, I don't understand anyone finding an excuse (unless you have a medical condition that prohibits wearing one) for not doing the three things that other countries who have slowed the spread have done.
1. Wear a mask
2. Social distance
3. Wash your hands frequently
From Angela:
By now most of us (hopefully) understand the necessity in wearing a mask to help slow the spread of COVID-19. We understand that it’s not just about protecting ourselves, it’s about protecting others.
As one who lived in Tokyo for many years wearing masks in public was and is a normal way of life.
Yes they do it to protect their own health, but it’s more out of a communal feeling of responsibility to care for others by not endangering them.
This inherent caring for others is part of why Japan has been successful in flattening the curve.
Here in CA we’re taking wearing masks to a new level.
We want to show that wearing a face mask 😷 is not just a community health statement worn in solidarity, but also how we can make face covering a fun and necessary accessory for your personal style.
You can match your mask to your outfit, or highlight your eye makeup look( as I did). 💗
Use your own unique, creative, artsy fun ways to show how you are making a mask/ face covering a staple in your life.
Remember to wear a mask & practice #socialdistancing wherever you go.
I have several masks that I wear depending on my mood-and for me it’s now a normal part of my daily routine.
By wearing a mask you’re not just keeping yourself safe, but others as well.
We’re in this together CALIFORNIA- now that #losangeles is back in lockdown again it’s imperative that we work together. So let’s show how we do it and inspire others to do the same. #youractionssavelives #slowthespread #stayhome #homequarantine @cagovernor Mask by Meredithe Herzog-Katz 🙏

Face masks have become an essential part of my wardrobe because we are all in this pandemic together. 💞 The best way to protect yourself, and keep others safe is by wearing a mask.  But why not make it fashion, consider face masks a part of your drip! 😷✨ Let’s all do our part, and get through this together! ❤️

When we talk, breathe, cough or sneeze droplets enter the air.  If we cover our nose and mouths we’re helping to stop those droplets from spreading to others, and stop others from spreading it to us.  One simple thing helps save lives, and that life might even be your own. 

I’m helping @CAgovernor @GavinNewsom spread the word about the importance of face coverings to slow the spread of Covid-19.  Be safe out there by living your best mask life and remember- #YourActionsSaveLives #SlowTheSpread
